Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.32,0:01:45.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.54,0:01:50.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm playing hide-and-seek\Nwith Naila and Eugene.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.66,0:01:53.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:01:58.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.34,0:02:01.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What we need to investigate now is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.34,0:02:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.59,0:02:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We know most of what we need to\Nabout the House.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.18,0:02:08.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The training is going well.\NThe tracking devices can be broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.31,0:02:09.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We just need...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.01,0:02:13.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}...to get intel on the outside,\Nand if we can outmaneuver the adults here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.48,0:02:15.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we can definitely clear the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.65,0:02:17.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next is checking out an escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.07,0:02:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}So this escape has three steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.36,0:02:23.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One, get over the wall and escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.86,0:02:27.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Two, get away from this farm safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.49,0:02:31.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Three, establish a way to survive outside\Nand become self-reliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:34.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Currently, we have hope\Nof accomplishing the first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:38.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next is the second step.\NWe need to focus on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:41.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Evade the pursuers\Nand get away from the farm safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.80,0:02:44.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We need to examine and prepare for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:46.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, we need information\Nabout the area around the farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.55,0:02:49.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, when I climbed up the tree,\NI saw a forest beyond the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.81,0:02:52.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the things\Nwe need to properly check.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:54.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We should look into it as soon as tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:55.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.48,0:02:58.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, can I talk about another thing\Nhaving to do with when we get outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.52,0:03:01.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have someone I want to introduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:09.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Mom. I'm in a rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:11.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.33,0:03:15.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.21,0:03:23.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:29.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The person I want to introduce is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.89,0:03:32.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.97,0:03:36.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. William Minerva?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:37.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.27,0:03:39.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:43.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. What I do know is that\Nhe's the previous owner of that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.23,0:03:46.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But he could be someone who's on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:48.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.41,0:03:52.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This person has been conveying\Na certain message through books.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.12,0:03:53.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And not just one book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.12,0:03:55.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Through many of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.42,0:04:06.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This symbol is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.97,0:04:08.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A bookplate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.09,0:04:11.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A label that indicates the book's owner\Nbefore it came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.39,0:04:13.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what's that certain message?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.47,0:04:14.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:18.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They all look like the same owl.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:20.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:22.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.65,0:04:27.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Morse code!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.95,0:04:28.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.73,0:05:05.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Run.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:08.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:10.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.82,0:05:13.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.45,0:05:17.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But with just this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.58,0:05:18.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What about these?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:21.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.46,0:05:24.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.46,0:05:26.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:28.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:33.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a message from the outside to us,\Nhidden from the demons and the adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.34,0:05:35.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think we can at least trust that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trust that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.72,0:05:39.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike her, I'm more suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:43.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This man named Minerva could be an ally to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.10,0:05:47.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't know if he's dead or alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.65,0:05:49.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We shouldn't get our hopes up too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.99,0:05:51.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you always like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.82,0:05:57.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,William Minerva. This man is outside\Nand knows our farm exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:01.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And though indirectly, he's trying to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.41,0:06:02.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.54,0:06:05.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was an ally on the outside.\NAnd he might still be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.38,0:06:10.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, then there could be\Na society of humans outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.05,0:06:11.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.90,0:06:36.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These kinds of messages\Ncan only be found in Minerva's books.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.74,0:06:40.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know when\Nthese labels were attached,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.16,0:06:44.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I at least know this one\Nwas attached after the year 2015.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.79,0:06:46.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:48.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything else we could know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:51.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like something in common between\Nthe contents or the type of books?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.34,0:06:52.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.84,0:06:55.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The genres are varied.\NThe publishers and the years were—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:58.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what about that thing?\NUh, which one was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.64,0:07:02.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand the Morse code\Non these two books.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:05.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the content,\None is a typical adventure novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:07.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and a mythology book\Nthat I didn't really understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:10.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no Morse code on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:11.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the other one is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.94,0:07:16.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:19.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.45,0:07:23.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.45,0:07:27.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it was true, what they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.79,0:07:31.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom was lying.\NNo one was sent to foster families.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:32.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.71,0:07:36.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because if they were,\Nthere's no way this would be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.59,0:07:38.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been delivered to Conny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.10,0:07:41.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just Little Bunny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.35,0:07:46.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They were all snatched away from them\Nby Mom when they left,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:49.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and they were all taken away by bad people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.27,0:07:51.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:00.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think these have a meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:05.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like how one book doesn't have the Morse code,\Nand there were others with ripped pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:07.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the message of "promise."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.54,0:08:09.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you think these two books are special?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.96,0:08:11.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I feel like...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.80,0:08:17.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,these will become some kind of\Nan important guide for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:18.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's your reasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:20.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My hunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.35,0:08:23.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me that look!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:28.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who is Mom communicating with?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:29.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The base Ray was talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:32.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are they the bad people?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.15,0:08:38.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, he said he had Mom under control,\Nbut we're doomed if Sister finds out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.86,0:08:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did he mean by doomed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.49,0:08:43.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they find out, is Mom or Sister\Ngoing to do something to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:48.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What if Mom is much more dangerous,\Nand Conny and our siblings are already...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.37,0:08:52.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it. Norman said he doesn't know\Nwhat happened to Conny.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.04,0:08:54.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. They're just hiding it from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.84,0:08:57.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They probably have a reason and can't tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.22,0:09:00.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe them like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.84,0:09:04.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because they don't believe in us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.47,0:09:08.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I think it's worth looking into.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.14,0:09:10.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Minerva and the mystery of his books.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.44,0:09:15.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not just running away.\NLet's find a way for us to survive in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.94,0:09:18.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Let's run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.07,0:09:20.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's live.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.95,0:09:23.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what the world is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.83,0:09:32.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Phil. I'll be there in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.25,0:09:37.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:39.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's expected from Ray\Nwho reads books all the time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.88,0:09:42.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For Emma to notice those bookplates...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.55,0:09:44.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't the one who noticed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.55,0:09:47.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil found them and told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.81,0:09:48.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.72,0:09:52.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He was reading a children’s book\Nand it was one of Mr. Minerva's.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:55.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was a book that had Morse code in the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.23,0:09:56.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you get the plates?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.40,0:09:59.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.07,0:10:00.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where are Don and Gilda?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:01.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're not here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.16,0:10:03.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.78,0:10:42.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.90,0:10:45.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. What’s wrong, Eugene?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:47.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I found this on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.20,0:10:53.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.63,0:11:00.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.63,0:11:03.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don. Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.97,0:11:06.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness, I thought you'd...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:22.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.40,0:11:25.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We went in to Mom's secret room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.15,0:11:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.61,0:11:28.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don stole the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.99,0:11:30.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.03,0:11:31.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And, did Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.87,0:11:36.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she noticed. We already\Nreturned the key, too. So probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.12,0:11:39.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You did something really stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.42,0:11:45.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do if the room was equipped\Nwith either a camera, a bug, or an alarm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.22,0:11:49.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Mom or Sister found out,\Nyou two... no, all of us would be—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:51.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us what would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.43,0:11:55.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would we get killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.10,0:11:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We found Conny's Little Bunny\Nin the secret room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:03.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So much for your "I don't know"\Nand "let's go save them".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.78,0:12:05.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can't even go save them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.32,0:12:08.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because Conny...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.82,0:12:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conny and everyone else is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.37,0:12:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.70,0:12:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.16,0:12:15.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So they're really...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.33,0:12:17.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:20.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They were lying after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.29,0:12:24.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you hiding? Tell us the whole truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:40.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Demons? A farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.81,0:12:44.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. Just to be eaten...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:48.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you're a spy? This whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:50.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was for our sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.16,0:12:54.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then Ray, you knew what was going\Nto happen to Conny that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:13:01.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma and Norman, you both tried to trick us\Nand take us out into a world full of enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.60,0:13:18.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:20.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Don!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:31.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.53,0:13:33.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are we that much of a burden?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.49,0:13:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are we that weak and useless to you\Nthat you feel the need to protect us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.25,0:13:46.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That time, when you asked us to help you,\NI thought you were relying on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.00,0:13:47.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was that a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.88,0:13:51.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not as smart as you three.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.30,0:13:53.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.97,0:13:56.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...aren't we family?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.10,0:13:58.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't we siblings?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.27,0:14:02.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just want you to have a little faith in us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.15,0:14:09.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I'm acting a little weird right now.\NI'm going to go cool off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:10.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.33,0:14:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:30.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:33.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just taking it out on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.34,0:14:36.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not frustrated because\Nthey treated us like weaklings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.05,0:14:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I made them lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.72,0:14:42.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't do anything\Nfor Conny and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.31,0:14:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ignorant and powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.81,0:14:50.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's frustrating because I really am a weakling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.15,0:14:52.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's so frustrating!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:56.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to become stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.29,0:15:01.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to become stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:02.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.54,0:15:07.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don! Gilda!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.54,0:15:09.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:15.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:21.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was prepared to be resented, but I didn't\Nhave enough resolve to believe in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.89,0:15:24.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.23,0:15:27.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.27,0:15:32.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, well, I'm also sorry\Nthat I suddenly punched you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.40,0:15:35.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay? You're not, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:36.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.78,0:15:40.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, too, about acting on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:43.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Of course Ray would get mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.62,0:15:45.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we're really...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.62,0:15:47.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:53.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.01,0:15:56.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the worst happens,\NI'll take care of it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.84,0:16:02.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also sorry for the other things I did.\NI apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.94,0:16:11.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don. Gilda. There's no more lying,\Nso let me ask again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.11,0:16:13.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we mess up, we die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.90,0:16:16.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The outside is, at worst, a world full of demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.24,0:16:19.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, will you run away with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.37,0:16:23.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:40.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I feel better now that we told them the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.47,0:16:42.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.06,0:16:47.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}One week until we carry out our plan.\NThe preparations are going well, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.06,0:16:49.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We just have to figure out\Nhow to escape with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.06,0:16:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey, Norman, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to figure out on my own\Nhow to escape with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:07.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it's reckless?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.54,0:17:08.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.71,0:17:11.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But with this plan,\Nwe can catch Mom off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.75,0:17:14.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Realistically, this is the only way\Nto escape with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.05,0:17:17.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.01,0:17:23.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should we tell Ray?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.72,0:17:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.85,0:17:28.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think Ray\Nwould really have everyone escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.43,0:17:29.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he would.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.06,0:17:33.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray's been moving all this time\Nwhile thinking about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.06,0:17:36.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Always, for the both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:37.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.65,0:17:42.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Don't worry.\NI'll bring it up to Ray sometime soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.57,0:17:43.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.31,0:18:13.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"All this to make sure\Nyou two don't get killed."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.98,0:18:18.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're amazing, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.65,0:18:23.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I stole them, just like you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:26.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Detergent and herbicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:28.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to use these for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.16,0:18:30.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They'll come in handy for our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:35.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By investigation, you mean we'll go past the fence\Nto climb the wall and look outside, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:38.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about the tracking devices?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.34,0:18:41.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to make sure\Nthey don't check them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:44.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have both Mom and Sister\Nlooking somewhere else,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:48.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and create a situation where they\Nwon't look at their trackers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:49.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:52.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have Ray stall Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.64,0:18:55.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having him give her false information.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.56,0:18:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you had a fight with that Norman?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.07,0:19:01.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We had a difference of opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.57,0:19:03.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.99,0:19:05.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norman is trying to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.16,0:19:12.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he wants to escape with everyone,\Nthat's something he would think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.66,0:19:13.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.46,0:19:15.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's collecting items.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.12,0:19:20.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A hammer, detergent, herbicide,\Nor anything else that he thinks he can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:22.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Including that rope that's too short?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.42,0:19:24.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I tried to stop him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:26.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told him it's too risky and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.80,0:19:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how you got that bruise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.93,0:19:32.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Murder by poison.\NChemicals can be troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.06,0:19:35.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You'd better not ship them out early.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want them to live to the end,\Nuntil 12 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.98,0:19:41.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this House, without any discomforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.69,0:19:45.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's replace the chemicals\Nwith something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.57,0:19:47.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Put fake stuff in the containers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.03,0:19:48.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.57,0:19:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah.\N- Then let's deal with this tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:52.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you have to report?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.87,0:19:55.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Do you have something else\Nthat's bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.00,0:19:56.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.54,0:19:58.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:01.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm letting you know a little early.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:05.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I received a notification from the top\Nat yesterday's scheduled check-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.05,0:20:06.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The next shipment has been set.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.18,0:20:10.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There will be no regular shipment\Nfor next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.22,0:20:13.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then the next one will be in January.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:15.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My 12th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.10,0:20:22.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the next shipment will finally be me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.74,0:20:29.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But even if we leave Ray to deal with Mom,\Nwhat about Sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.74,0:20:33.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if she finds out,\Nwe'll be shipped out immediately, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:35.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:48.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:52.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:58.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching the whole thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:03.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Talking in the dining hall last night,\Nall of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.73,0:21:06.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The ones who know the secret\Nabout this House
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.15,0:21:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is Norman, Emma, Ray, Gilda, and Don.\NThe five of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.99,0:21:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:18.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,would you like to join forces?
